This paper is primarily focused on the analysis and optimization of convolutional neural network architectures for computer vision tasks, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses techniques for topology construction and evaluation, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper explores the impact of data augmentation and test-time transformations on accuracy, which relates to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
